turn.1: What is the Seven Stars in Kyushu The?
turn.2: Seven Stars in Kyushu The is a deluxe sleeping car excursion train operated by Kyushu Railway Company (JR Kyushu) in Japan since October 2013.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: The overall design concept of the train was overseen by industrial designer Eiji Mitooka.
turn.6: The name of the train is derived from the seven prefectures of Kyushu and the fact that the train is made up of seven cars.
turn.7: What did you find interesting about the design?
turn.8: The dedicated diesel locomotive, DF200-7000, for the train was built by Kawasaki Heavy Industries in Kobe, based on the JR Freight Class DF200 locomotive, modified for use in Kyushu and finished in a livery of deep maroon.
turn.11: What were some of the highlights?
turn.12: The coaches are based on the 817 series EMU body design and are mounted on 787 series EMU bogies.
